        <updateDate>2024-09-12T13:04:21Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Protecting Charitable Giving Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill increases the penalty for the unauthorized disclosure of the identities of donors to tax-exempt organizations from a maximum of $5,000 to between $10,000 and $250,000. It&amp;nbsp; also modifies venue rules to allow prosecution of offenses in the judicial district in which a victim of an offense resides.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
